pets.name: Samy
pets.description:
His name is Samy, who was received by a veterinary group because he was at risk. She lived on the street and took refuge from time to time in a cardboard box, her body was marked by abandonment, suffering and indifference.
She suffered from distemper, parasites, scabies, malnutrition and other diseases, it is very sad to see such a depressing state of an animal that she is not to blame for anything. During the first year Samy she was in a very bad state, she was not sure if she could be saved.

After a while, Samy began to improve markedly, and the positive results of the intensive care she underwent began to be seen. Today Samy is super happy in her new home.

pets.name: Lucero
pets.description:
Her name is Lucero. She was rescued by a dog care group in a somewhat sad situation in that she was unable to walk due to an injury to her spine and hip.

Lucero never gave up until she finally took her first steps on the right path. Despite her hip dysplasia, Lucero is able to walk and run like any other dog and she is very happy at the shelter.

pets.name: Loba
pets.description:
They found her in a very critical condition, it was really very difficult to think that she could be saved, she suffered from scabies, extreme malnutrition among other infections, but with the help of good people and the will to live of this beautiful dog she was able to defeat death.

After a few months of recovery she was adopted by a family and is happy and running around the garden with other dogs.

pets.name: Domitilia
pets.description: Before calling herself Domitila and having a family, 'Domi' was rescued after living for several years in a market in San Juan de Miraflores. When she was found, she had almost no hair and her body was full of scabies, fungus and bacteria. "She fed herself with the leftovers that she found at the food stalls," says Anais Anaya, rescuer and founder of Animal Voice, one of the shelters affiliated with WUF.

pets.name: Zeus
pets.description: Zeus had to live out several years of his old age on the streets. He was just rescued this 2020 thanks to the Animal Voice team. “We found him next to a kitten in San Martín de Porres. Apparently, someone abandoned them in the street”, explains Anais. When they picked him up, he had malnutrition, spinal problems, anemia, pneumonia, canine ehrlichia, and was infested with ticks and fleas.

shelters.name: Voz Animal
shelters.description: Our mission is to sterilize street animals, as a solution to the problem of overpopulation and abandonment of these animals. That is why we carry out monthly sterilization campaigns in districts with vulnerable populations.

shelters.name: Wuf
shelters.description: We are a non-profit association that seeks to build a better world for dogs through sustainable initiatives.

shelters.name: Animazul
shelters.description: The Animazul shelter currently houses 43 puppies, most of them already old, and is maintained thanks to the help of the padrinoazules who contribute an amount per month. There are many needs in the shelter. On this, our website, you can learn about the puppies we care for and the ways you can help them. We invite you to see the various pages and meet our "refugees", perhaps you will be encouraged to sponsor them or you can provide them with a home.

shelters.name: Proa
shelters.description: Be part of this beautiful initiative to help dogs and cats located in "La casa de Doguito" in Chorrillos. Our main task is to bring as many donations as possible to the animals that are refugees, they eagerly await to be visited. Cheer up to work with us and be able to #ChangeYourBadDays!
